Rating: 4
I made this tonight with roasted garlic (about 7 cloves) with 3lbs of white potatoes, cut in wedges. I tossed in (along with original ingredients) some white wine vinager (1tsp), 1/2 a chopped onion, 4 pats of butter on top, (fat is flovor!) some (sprinkle) montreal steak seasoning, a bit of sugar (why not?!), some kosher salt, fresh pepper, and chopped parsley. I cooked it about 10-15 minutes longer then stated, because I like mine nice and crisp, (all at 500 degrees) turning the potatoes every 10 minutes or so. It was amazing!!!! crunchy, carmelized onions on the outside, soft "mashed potatoes" on the inside, I made enough for some leftovers, but I have picked and picked and this wont make it past breakfast tomorrow morning! Would make a GREAT breakfast potatoe!

