I made this recipe to serve as a side dish to a prime rib roast. I minced the garlic instead of slicing it and added salt and pepper. I added some peeled boiler onions about 1/2 way through the cooking time. I cooked it at 500 until I added the onions. It was getting pretty smoky in my oven, so I turned it down to 450. Very tasty and easy.

